docs.abstract: Unlike most other Silicon Valley darlings going public this year, Slack is not holding an initial public offering, where it sells shares to the public.
docs.snippet: Unlike most other Silicon Valley darlings going public this year, Slack is not holding an initial public offering, where it sells shares to the public.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Slack, the workplace messaging start-up, disclosed the details of its business in an offering prospectus on Friday as it joined the parade of tech companies that plan to publicly list their shares this year.

headline.main: Slack Discloses $141 Million Loss as Messaging Start-Up Joins Tech Listing Rush
headline.print_headline: Slack Reports Big Loss  Before Its Direct Listing

docs.abstract: Innovation, investment and inviting geology have given new life to an oil patch that once seemed spent. The oil field is now the world’s second most productive.
docs.snippet: Innovation, investment and inviting geology have given new life to an oil patch that once seemed spent. The oil field is now the world’s second most productive.
docs.lead_paragraph: MIDLAND, Tex. — In a global collapse of oil prices five years ago, scores of American oil companies went bankrupt. But one field withstood the onslaught, and even thrived: the Permian Basin, straddling Texas and New Mexico.

headline.main: The ‘Monster’ Texas Oil Field That Made the U.S. a Star in the World Market
headline.print_headline: ‘Monster’ Texas Field Revives U.S. Oil Fortunes

docs.abstract: In tight labor markets, developers and local leaders are using major projects to provide residents with careers in construction.
docs.snippet: In tight labor markets, developers and local leaders are using major projects to provide residents with careers in construction.
docs.lead_paragraph: A year ago, Jeromy Gaviola was struggling to find steady and meaningful work in San Francisco. Living in the working-class neighborhood of Hunters Point, he heard about a program that was training residents to build the Chase Center, the $1 billion, 18,000-seat arena in Mission Bay that will be the new home of the Golden State Warriors when it opens this fall.

headline.main: Some Workers Need Jobs as Much as Builders Need Workers. Cities Connect Them.
headline.print_headline: Help Wanted, Work Boots and Skills Provided

docs.abstract: The global consulting firm McKinsey is accused of violating the law when it simultaneously advises and has a financial interest in bankrupt companies.
docs.snippet: The global consulting firm McKinsey is accused of violating the law when it simultaneously advises and has a financial interest in bankrupt companies.
docs.lead_paragraph: At first glance, it didn’t look like a fair fight. On one side: an enormous and powerful global consulting company. On the other: the retired founder of a smaller turnaround firm who has become a thorn in the side of its larger rival.

headline.main: McKinsey Faces a Perilous Fight in a Texas Bankruptcy Case
headline.print_headline: McKinsey Faces Perilous Fight In Texas Court

docs.abstract: The consulting firm is the subject of another complaint by a retired turnaround specialist who accused McKinsey of working with a bankrupt company to improperly route its payments.
docs.snippet: The consulting firm is the subject of another complaint by a retired turnaround specialist who accused McKinsey of working with a bankrupt company to improperly route its payments.
docs.lead_paragraph: McKinsey & Company, a consulting firm whose conduct in bankruptcy cases has already drawn the attention of two judges, was accused before a third on Tuesday of improperly receiving and concealing payments from a client on the verge of bankruptcy. This raised the prospect that the judge overseeing the case could order the return of tens of millions of dollars in fees earned by the consulting company.

headline.main: McKinsey & Company Is Again Accused of Misdeeds in Bankruptcy Case
headline.print_headline: McKinsey Faces Accusation That It Concealed Payments
